```rust
fn exit_with_state(code: i32) -> ! {
    let status = if code == 0 { "completed" } else { "error" };
    if code != 0 {
        // Include caller location info
        let loc = std::panic::Location::caller();
        state::stash_diagnostic_error(&format!("exit({}) at {}:{}", code, loc.file(), loc.line()));
        state::mark_run_completed_with_error(&format!("exit code {}", code));
    } else {
        state::mark_run_completed(status);
    }
    std::process::exit(code);
}
```

This would give us the file and line of every `exit_with_state` call, making it much easier to diagnose WHERE crashes happen, even without context-specific messages. This is a one-function change.

